<paragraph id="8B8D3B1EFFB6FFD26CE4F880FEA05D5F" blockId="1.[151,1436,1837,2044]" box="[151,262,1875,1899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">
(
<figureCitation id="1309279BFFB6FFD26CECF880FF5B5D5F" box="[159,253,1875,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1568,1590]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,559,1539]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,559,1539]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hoplothrips species. H. hongruiae sp. n. 1–5: (1) Head &amp; pronotum; (2) Antenna; (3) Male sternite VIII; (4) Pelta &amp; tergites II–III; (5) Prosternum &amp; mesopresternum. (6) H. fungosus prosternites. Antennal segments III–IV 7–8: (7) H. corticis; (8) H. orientalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3734659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3734659/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Figs 1–5</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D3B1EFFB6FFD16CE4F8A4FBDD582E" blockId="1.[151,1436,1837,2044]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,154,538]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="598" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis id="B946E70CFFB6FFD26CE4F8A4FECD5DBB" box="[151,363,1911,1935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. Body and femora brown, basal half of tube darker; tarsi and apex of tibiae yellow; antennal segment III mainly yellow, IV–V variably yellow at base; fore wings pale; major setae brown. Head (
<figureCitation id="1309279BFFB6FFD268D8F848FB4F5D87" box="[1195,1257,1947,1971]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1568,1590]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,559,1539]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,559,1539]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hoplothrips species. H. hongruiae sp. n. 1–5: (1) Head &amp; pronotum; (2) Antenna; (3) Male sternite VIII; (4) Pelta &amp; tergites II–III; (5) Prosternum &amp; mesopresternum. (6) H. fungosus prosternites. Antennal segments III–IV 7–8: (7) H. corticis; (8) H. orientalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3734659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3734659/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) with transverse polygonal sculpture near base, without distinct sculpture on anterior half; cheeks widest behind eyes, narrowing to base; compound eyes about one third of head length; postocular setae capitate, much shorter than dorsal eye length; ocelli well developed; postocellar setae pointed, longer than the diameter of posterior ocelli; maxillary stylets retracted to postocular setae, 0.2–0.3 of head width apart medially, with distinct maxillary bridge. Antennae 8-segmented (
<figureCitation id="1309279BFFB5FFD168BAFF6DFAAD5AE2" box="[1225,1291,190,214]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1568,1590]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,559,1539]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,559,1539]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hoplothrips species. H. hongruiae sp. n. 1–5: (1) Head &amp; pronotum; (2) Antenna; (3) Male sternite VIII; (4) Pelta &amp; tergites II–III; (5) Prosternum &amp; mesopresternum. (6) H. fungosus prosternites. Antennal segments III–IV 7–8: (7) H. corticis; (8) H. orientalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3734659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3734659/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), segment III with 2 slender sense cones, IV with 4 sense cones, VIII broad at base and much shorter than VII. Pronotum with weak transverse sculpture near posterior margin; with 5 pairs of capitate major setae (
<figureCitation id="1309279BFFB5FFD16F86FED5FB935B2A" box="[1013,1077,262,286]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1568,1590]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,559,1539]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,559,1539]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hoplothrips species. H. hongruiae sp. n. 1–5: (1) Head &amp; pronotum; (2) Antenna; (3) Male sternite VIII; (4) Pelta &amp; tergites II–III; (5) Prosternum &amp; mesopresternum. (6) H. fungosus prosternites. Antennal segments III–IV 7–8: (7) H. corticis; (8) H. orientalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3734659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3734659/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum with transverse reticulation on anterior half, lateral setae weakly capitate; metanotum with weak polygonal sculpture, median setae acute. Prosternum (
<figureCitation id="1309279BFFB5FFD16D50FE9DFEC05B51" box="[291,358,333,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1568,1590]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,559,1539]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,559,1539]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hoplothrips species. H. hongruiae sp. n. 1–5: (1) Head &amp; pronotum; (2) Antenna; (3) Male sternite VIII; (4) Pelta &amp; tergites II–III; (5) Prosternum &amp; mesopresternum. (6) H. fungosus prosternites. Antennal segments III–IV 7–8: (7) H. corticis; (8) H. orientalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3734659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3734659/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) with basantra weakly indicated by variable coalescence of some chitinous islets; ferna triangular almost meeting medially; mesopresternum complete; mesoeusternal anterior margin entire. Fore tarsal tooth absent. Fore wing parallel sided, with three sub-basal setae, S1 and S2 capitate, S3 longest and pointed, 4 duplicated cilia. Pelta with weak sculpture and small lateral lobes (
<figureCitation id="1309279BFFB5FFD16E48FE69FDDB5BE6" box="[571,637,442,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1568,1590]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,559,1539]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,559,1539]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Hoplothrips species. H. hongruiae sp. n. 1–5: (1) Head &amp; pronotum; (2) Antenna; (3) Male sternite VIII; (4) Pelta &amp; tergites II–III; (5) Prosternum &amp; mesopresternum. (6) H. fungosus prosternites. Antennal segments III–IV 7–8: (7) H. corticis; (8) H. orientalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3734659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3734659/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), campaniform sensilla located almost on margin; tergites II–VII each with two pairs of sigmoid wing-retaining setae; sternites each with 3–5 pairs of discal setae; tergite VIII median setae capitate; tergite IX setae S1 much shorter than tube and blunt, S2 pointed; anal setae shorter than tube.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF4D6B96FFB5FFD16CE4F9F3FF5F5C4A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3734659" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3734659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3734659/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="598" startId="2.[151,258,1568,1590]" targetBox="[151,1429,559,1539]" targetPageId="2">
